  "plainText": "Don't Starve\nTogether\nExclusive to:\nBanana Pop\nFood Info\n12.5\n20\n33\nVeggie\nObject Info\nPerk\nLowers temperature by 10 degrees over 10 seconds.\n3 Days\nCan be Burned\n40\nCooking Info\nx1.0 /x1.0 x1.0 x1.0\n10 sec\n20\nMiscellaneous\n\"bananapop\"\n“No, not brain freeze! I need that for science!”\n–Wilson\n“This is the opposite of burning.”\n–Willow\n“Wolfgang can eat in one bite!”\n–Wolfgang\n“I used to eat these with Abigail...”\n–Wendy\n“STICK ADDON INSTALLED”\n–WX-78\n“Well, isn't that refreshing?”\n–Wickerbottom\n“I'd prefer maple taffy...”\n–Woodie\n“Hm... I don't know what I was expecting.”\n–Maxwell\n“Quite efficient in lowering my internal temperature. Tastes good too.”\n–Wagstaff\n“I've sömehöw föund a way tö make it even LESS appealing!”\n–Wigfrid\n“Yaaay! Popsicle, popsicle!”\n–Webber\n“The best way to keep cool. And very little preparation!”\n–Walani\n“Perhaps not my most complicated dish, but no less tasty.”\n–Warly\n“'Nonos!”\n–Wilbur\n“I heard ther be gold in th'banana stand.”\n–Woodlegs\n“'TIS A NUMMIES'”\n–Wilba\n“Frozen friend hair”\n–Wormwood\n“Banana. Stick. Ice. What more do you need?”\n–Wheeler\n“Cool and refreshin'!”\n–Winona\n“Hyuyu, what will the mortals think of next.”\n–Wortox\n“Fruit taste even better on stick!”\n–Wurt\n“Those are for little kids. But bananas are healthy so I guess it's alright.”\n–Walter\n“There's nothing quicker and simpler than fruit on a stick.”\n–Wanda\nBanana Pop is a Crock Pot recipe introduced in the Shipwrecked DLC. It is made from 1 Raw Banana, 1 Ice, and 1 Twig or Dorsal Fin. It is a great Sanity restoring food, as Ice can be plentiful from refining Hail during the Hurricane Season or using an Ice Maker 3000.\nIts cooking ingredients cannot contain any kind of Meats or Fish. Adding Wobster, Shark Fin, Jellyfish, Fishes or Meats will result in Lobster Bisque, Shark Fin Soup, Jelly-O Pop, Fishsticks and Kabobs respectively.\nIt restores 20 , 12.5 , and 33 , and reduces body temperature by 1 degree per second for 10 seconds.\nAs a non-meat item, Wigfrid cannot eat it.\nPrerequisites[edit | edit source]\nRequires:\nRequires:\nRequires:\nExcludes:\nExcludes:\nRecipe[edit | edit source]\nExamples[edit | edit source]\n×2\nA recipe for Banana Pop that extenuates hunger value.\nTrivia[edit | edit source]\nBanana Pop with adjusted recipe was added to Don't Starve Together in the Warly Character Update.\nThe Banana Pop is one of the few items in the game with examination quotes for Wilbur.\nGallery[edit | edit source]\nIcon used as emoji for Official Klei Discord\nBy TypeBy Crock Pot Value\nView or edit this template\nFood and Edible Items (by Food Type)\nVeggie\nSeeds\nMeat\nGoodies\nGeneric\nHorrible\nRoughage\nElementals\nBurnt\nRaw\nGears\nGold Dust\nBerry\nWood\nNitre\nLunar Shards\nView or edit this template\nFood and Edible Items (by Food Value)\nMeats\nFishes\nVegetables\nFruits\nMonster Food\nEggs\nDairy\nSweetener\nFrozen\nInedibles\nMagic\nFat\nSeed\nJellyfish\nBone\nFilter\nAntihistamine\nDecoration\nBug\nNo Value Food",
