  "wikitext": "{{Navbutton/Separation}}\n{{Exclusivity|Shipwrecked|Don't Starve Together}}\n{{Object Infobox\n|foodType = [[Veggie]] [[File:Veggie.png|32px|]]\n|foodRecipe ={{Pic|32px|Banana SW}}x1.0 {{Pic|32px|Twigs}}/{{Pic|32px|Dorsal Fin}}x1.0 {{Pic|32px|Ice}}x1.0 {{Pic|32px|Filler}}x1.0\n|icon = Banana Pop.png\n|image = Banana Pop Dropped.png\n|hpRestored     = 20\n|hungerRestored = 12.5\n|sanityRestored = 33\n|cooktime       = 10 sec\n|priority       = 20\n|spoil          = 3 Days\n|perk           = Lowers temperature by 10 degrees over 10 seconds.\n|stack          = 40\n|spawnCode      = \"bananapop\"\n|canBeBurned=1\n}}\n{{BananaQuotes\n|wilson = No, not brain freeze! I need that for science!\n|willow = This is the opposite of burning.\n|wolfgang = Wolfgang can eat in one bite!\n|wendy = I used to eat these with Abigail...\n|wx78 = STICK ADDON INSTALLED\n|wickerbottom = Well, isn't that refreshing?\n|woodie = I'd prefer maple taffy...\n|maxwell = Hm... I don't know what I was expecting.\n|wagstaff = Quite efficient in lowering my internal temperature. Tastes good too.\n|wigfrid = I've sömehöw föund a way tö make it even LESS appealing!\n|webber = Yaaay! Popsicle, popsicle!\n|walani = The best way to keep cool. And very little preparation!\n|warly = Perhaps not my most complicated dish, but no less tasty.\n|wilbur = 'Nonos!\n|woodlegs = I heard ther be gold in th'banana stand.\n|wilba = 'TIS A NUMMIES'\n|wormwood = Frozen friend hair\n|wheeler = Banana. Stick. Ice. What more do you need?\n|winona = Cool and refreshin'!\n|wortox = Hyuyu, what will the mortals think of next.\n|wurt = Fruit taste even better on stick!\n|walter = Those are for little kids. But bananas are healthy so I guess it's alright.\n|wanda = There's nothing quicker and simpler than fruit on a stick.\n|choose = wendy}}\n'''Banana Pop''' is a [[Crock Pot]] recipe introduced in the ''[[Don't Starve: Shipwrecked|Shipwrecked]]'' DLC. It is made from 1 [[Banana|Raw Banana]], 1 [[Ice]], and 1 [[Twigs|Twig]] or [[Dorsal Fin]]. It is a great [[Sanity]] restoring food, as Ice can be plentiful from refining [[Hail]] during the [[Hurricane Season]] or using an [[Ice Maker 3000]].\n\nIts cooking ingredients cannot contain any kind of [[Meats]] or [[Fishes|Fish]]. Adding [[Wobster]], [[Shark Fin]], [[Jellyfish]], [[Fishes]] or [[Meats]] will result in [[Lobster Bisque]], [[Shark Fin Soup]], [[Jelly-O Pop]], [[Fishsticks]] and [[Kabobs]] respectively.\n\nIt restores 20 {{Hp}}, 12.5 {{Hunger}}, and 33 {{Sanity}}, and reduces body temperature by 1 degree per second for 10 seconds. \n\nAs a non-meat item, [[Wigfrid]] cannot eat it.\n\n== Prerequisites ==\n* Requires: [[File:Banana SW.png|link=Banana]]\n* Requires:[[File:Twigs.png]] \n* Requires: [[File:Ice.png|link=Ice]]\n* Excludes: [[File:Meats Crock Pot.png|link=Meats]]\n* Excludes: [[File:Fishes Crock Pot.png|link=Fishes]]\n\n== {{pic32|Cookbook}} Recipe ==\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Banana SW\n|item2 = Ice\n|item3 = Twigs\n|item4 = Filler\n|tool = Crock Pot\n|result = Banana Pop}}\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Banana SW\n|item2 = Ice\n|item3 = Dorsal Fin\n|item4 = Filler\n|tool = Crock Pot\n|result = Banana Pop}}\n\n=={{Pic|32|Icon Science}} Examples ==\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Banana SW\n|item2 = Ice\n|item3 = Twigs\n|count3 = 2\n|tool = Crock Pot\n|result = Banana Pop\n|note={{Pic24|Prototype}} A recipe for Banana Pop that extenuates hunger value.}}\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Banana SW\n|item2 = Ice\n|item3 = Dorsal Fin\n|item4 = Seaweed\n|tool = Crock Pot\n|result = Banana Pop\n|dlc =\n}}\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Banana SW\n|item2 = Ice\n|item3 = Twigs\n|item4 = Berries\n|tool = Crock Pot\n|result = Banana Pop\n}}\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Banana SW\n|item2 = Ice\n|item3 = Twigs\n|item4 = Nightmare Fuel\n|tool = Crock Pot\n|result = Banana Pop\n}}\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Banana SW\n|item2 = Ice\n|item3 = Twigs\n|item4 = Bone Shards\n|tool = Crock Pot\n|result = Banana Pop\n}}\n\n== {{Pic32|Placeholder}} Trivia ==\n* Banana Pop with adjusted recipe was added to ''Don't Starve Together'' in the [[Don't Starve Together/Version History#July 25, 2019 - Warly Character Update|Warly Character Update]].\n* The Banana Pop is one of the few items in the game with examination quotes for [[Wilbur]].\n== {{Pic|32|Blueprint}} Gallery ==\n<gallery>\nBanana Pop 128x128.png|Icon used as emoji for Official Klei Discord\n</gallery>\n{{Crock Pot Food}}\n[[es:Palito de banana]]\n[[fr:sucette de banane]]\n__NOTOC__\n[[Category:Food]]\n[[Category:Perishables]]\n[[Category:Healing]]\n[[Category:Sanity Boost]]\n[[Category:Cooling]]\n[[Category:Crock Pot Recipes]]\n[[Category:Flammable Objects]]\n[[Category:Items]]\n[[vi:Banana Pop]]"
